[0.001, "o", "\u001b[39;49m\u001b[37m\u001b[40m\u001b[H\u001b[2J\u001b(B\u001b[0;7m\u001b[39;49m\u001b[37m\u001b[40mMorning Prayer - May 7, 2026 - Collect (1/6) \u001b[7bh/l section  j/k scroll  m note  ? help  q quit\r\n\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[39;49m\u001b[37m\u001b[40mA Collect\r\n-\u001b[8b\r\nO Lord, our heavenly Father, almighty and everlasting God, you have brought us\r\nsafely to the beginning of this day: Defend us by your mighty power, that we\r\nmay not fall into sin nor run into any danger; and that, guided by your\r\nSpirit, we may do what is righteous in your sight; through Jesus Christ our\r\nLord. Amen."]
[1.067, "o", "\u001b[1;32H\u001b(B\u001b[0;7m\u001b[39;49m\u001b[37m\u001b[40mPsalm 12 (2/6)\r\n\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[39;49m\u001b[37m\u001b[40mPsalm\u001b[K\r\nPsalm 12\u001b[K\r\n-\u001b[7b\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\nPsalms 12\u001b[K\r\n1. Help, LORD; for the godly man ceaseth; for the faithful fail from among the\r\n    children of men.\r\n2. They speak vanity every one with his neighbour: with flattering lips and\n\u001b[5Gwith a double heart do they speak.\r\n3. The LORD shall cut off all flattering lips, and the tongue that speaketh\n\u001b[5Gproud things:\r\n4. Who have said, With our tongue will we prevail; our lips are our own: who\n\u001b[5Gis lord over us?\r\n5. For the oppression of the poor, for the sighing of the needy, now will I\n\u001b[5Garise, saith the LORD; I will set him in safety from him that puffeth at\n\u001b[5Ghim.\r\n6. The words of the LORD are pure words: as silver tried in a furnace of\n\u001b[5Gearth, purified seven times.\r\n7. Thou shalt keep them, O LORD, thou shalt preserve them from this generation\n\u001b[5Gfor ever.\r\n8. The wicked walk on every side, when the vilest men are exalted."]
[1.838, "o", "\r\u001b[17d\u001b[J\u001b[1;39H\u001b(B\u001b[0;7m\u001b[39;49m\u001b[37m\u001b[40m3 (3\n\n\u001b[8G\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[39;49m\u001b[37m\u001b[40m3\n\n\n3\n\u001b[5Gow long wilt thou forget me, O LORD? for ever? how long wilt thou hide thy\n\u001b[5Gface from me?\u001b[K\r\n2. How long shall I take counsel in my soul, having sorrow in my heart daily?\n\u001b[5Ghow long shall mine enemy be exalted over me?\r\n3. Consider and hear me, O LORD my God: lighten mine eyes, lest I sleep the\n\u001b[5Gsleep of death;\r\n4. Lest mine enemy say, I have prevailed against him; and those that trouble\n\u001b[5Gme rejoice when I am moved.\r\n5. But I have trusted in thy mercy; my heart shall rejoice in thy salvation.\r\n6. I will sing unto the LORD, because he hath dealt bountifully with me.\u001b[K"]
[1.507, "o", "\u001b[1;39H\u001b(B\u001b[0;7m\u001b[39;49m\u001b[37m\u001b[40m4 (4\n\n\u001b[8G\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[39;49m\u001b[37m\u001b[40m4\n\n\n4\r\n1. The fool hath said in his heart, There is no God. They are corrupt, they\u001b[K\n\u001b[5Ghave done abominable works, there is none that doeth good.\r\n2. The LORD looked down from heaven upon the children of men, to see if there\n\u001b[5Gwere any that did understand, and seek God.\u001b[K\r\n3. They are all gone aside, they are all together become filthy: there is none\n\u001b[5Gthat doeth good, no, not one.\r\n4. Have all the workers of iniquity no knowledge? who eat up my people as they\n\u001b[5Geat bread, and call not upon the LORD.\r\n5. There were they in great fear: for God is in the generation of the\u001b[K\r\n    righteous.\u001b[K\r\n6. Ye have shamed the counsel of the poor, because the LORD is his refuge.\r\n7. Oh that the salvation of Israel were come out of Zion! when the LORD\n\u001b[5Gbringeth back the captivity of his people, Jacob shall rejoice, and Israel\n\u001b[5Gshall be glad."]
